5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 796, L.D. 1221, “RESOLUTION,
10 Proposing an Amendment to the Constitution of Maine to Prohibit the Legislature from
11 Using Paid Family and Medical Leave Program Funds for Any Other Purpose”
12 Amend the resolution by striking out the title and substituting the following:
13 'Resolve, Directing the Department of Labor to Study Protection of Paid Family and
14 Medical Leave Benefits Program Funds'
15 Amend the resolution by striking out everything after the title and inserting the
16 following:
17 'Sec. 1. Department of Labor to study methods of protecting paid family
18 and medical leave benefits program funds. Resolved: That the Department of
19 Labor shall study methods to protect all revenues derived from taxes, fees, premiums, fines
20 and penalties relating to the paid family and medical leave benefits program under the
21 Maine Revised Statutes, Title 26, chapter 7, subchapter 6-C from being expended for any
22 purpose other than the paid family and medical leave benefits program. The department
23 shall submit its report, including any suggested legislation, to the Joint Standing Committee
24 on Labor no later than January 15, 2026. The Joint Standing Committee on Labor may
25 report out a bill to the Second Regular Session of the 132nd Legislature.'
26 Amend the resolution by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or
27 section number to read consecutively.
28 SUMMARY
2299 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, replaces the resolution
3300 with a resolve. The resolve directs the Department of Labor to study methods to protect
3311 paid family and medical leave benefits program funds from being expended for any purpose
3322 other than the paid family and medical leave benefits program.
3333 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
